    <!-- PlaceHolder tag prevents inline radmenu.ClientID code below clashing with Utility.EnsureScriptManager(this); -->
    <script>

        $(document).ready(function () {
            giveAllMenuLinksAUniqueIdentifier();
            $(".rmLink").on("keydown", setSpacebarToOpenMenus);
        });

        function giveAllMenuLinksAUniqueIdentifier() {
            //Give all menu items a unique attribute value so that I can identify them when spacebar is clicked. Same 'menunumber' attribute is set in .aspx code on menu items.
            var index = 0;
            $(".telerik_main_menu li.rmItem a.rmLink").each(function (index) {
                $(this).attr("menunumber", index);
            });
        }

        function setSpacebarToOpenMenus(e) {
            //Open submenus on spacebar press. 
            var theKey = e.which;
            if (theKey == 32) { // 32 is keycode for spacebar. 
                var menuNumber = $(this).attr("menunumber");
                var menu = $find("ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_ctl01_radmenu");
                var menuItem = menu.findItemByAttribute("menunumber", menuNumber);
                var submenuItems = menuItem.get_items();
                if (submenuItems.get_count() > 0) {
                    if (menuItem.get_isOpen() == false) {
                        menuItem.open();
                        e.preventDefault();
                    };
                };
            };
        };

        function ClickItem(menu, args) {
            //Event set in OnClientItemClicking="ClickItem";
            //When user clicks (presses Enter key) a menu item, if submenu is not open, then open it; otherwise navigate to the item's link. 
            var item = args.get_item();
            var submenuItems = item.get_items();
            if (submenuItems.get_count() > 0) {
                //If submenu is closed, then open it; otherwise click the menu item link. 
                if (item.get_isOpen() == false) {
                    args.set_cancel(true); //Cancel the default click action so that it doesn't trigger the menu item's navigation link.
                    item.open();
                }
                else {
                    if (typeof item.redirectToLink == 'undefined') {
                        item.redirectToLink = true;
                        item.click();
                    } else {
                        delete item.redirectToLink;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

    </script>

<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">

    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;

    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;

    mso-bidi-font-style:italic"><a href="#Travel_and_Visa_Process">Travel &amp; Visa Process</a></span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;

    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic"><a href="#Departure">Departure</a></span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic"><a href="#Unlawful_Presence">Unlawful Presence</a></span></li>

<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%; color: rgb(64, 190, 160);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Work_Authorization">Work Authorization</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Work only in the authorized place(s) of
    employment described in the I-129 petition filed with USCIS and for the
    period approved on your I-797.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Do not accept additional employment or work at
    an additional location without consulting with OIS in advance.&nbsp; </span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">You can have more than one H-1B sponsor, but
    this requires a separate I-129 filing.&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Have the department notify OIS if significant
    changes in duties, responsibilities, salary, or work site are expected
    during your authorized employment.&nbsp; An amended petition may be
    necessary.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><strong><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Immigration_Documents">Immigration Documents</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Maintain a valid passport at all times, valid
    for at least six months into the future.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Retain copies of all immigration documents
    including: current and expired passports, Forms I-797, I-94, etc.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">The I-797 approval notice is your property; there is a fee to request a duplicate I-797
    approval notice, if lost.
    </span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">If you changed from another immigration status
    or H employer, notify your last institution of your UIC H-1B.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">I-94</span></strong><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:italic">: </span></li>
    <ul style="margin-top:0in" type="circle">
        <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:
        .0001pt;mso-list:l1 level2 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
        mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Always review and save your </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="http://www.cbp.gov/I94"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;
        mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">new I-94</span></a></span><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:italic"> after
        reentry.&nbsp; </span></li>
        <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:
        .0001pt;mso-list:l1 level2 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
        mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Form I-94 must indicate "Admitted as:
        H-1B" and &ldquo;Admitted until date&rdquo; matching your I-797 H-1B approval
        notice, or an additional 10 days.&nbsp; </span></li>
        <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:
        .0001pt;mso-list:l1 level2 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
        mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Incorrect end date: If your I-94 indicates
        any other&nbsp;expiration date, contact OIS.&nbsp;Passport expiry within
        six month is a common reason for a shortened I-94.&nbsp; If this occurs,
        your work authorization and status are shortened to this date and we must
        work to re-extend your status as soon as possible.</span></li>
    </ul>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="H-1B_Validity_Period">H-1B Validity Period</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Maximum duration is six years, some exceptions
    apply.&nbsp; </span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Renewals</span></strong><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:italic">: </span></li>
    <ul style="margin-top:0in" type="circle">
        <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:
        .0001pt;mso-list:l1 level2 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
        mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Your department will need to initiate the H-1
        B extension process (if eligible) 4-6 months prior to your H-1B expiry
        date. </span></li>
    </ul>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Recapture</span></strong><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:italic">: </span></li>
    <ul style="margin-top:0in" type="circle">
        <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:
        .0001pt;mso-list:l1 level2 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
        mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Time outside of the United States may be
        &ldquo;recaptured.&rdquo;&nbsp;Keep copies of all documentation of your time outside
        of the country in the event you need to extend your H-1B beyond six
        years.</span></li>
    </ul>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;margin-bottom:.0001pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="H-4_Dependents">H-4 Dependents</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Generally, H-4 dependents are not eligible to
    work, or volunteer to work.&nbsp; They may attend school.&nbsp; Some H-4s
    may apply for work authorization in certain cases.&nbsp; Consult OIS if
    you have questions. </span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Address_Changes">Address Changes</h2>
</strong><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"></span>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Report any change in residential address,
    within 10 days of moving, to USCIS (</span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="http://www.uscis.gov/portal/site/uscis/menuitem.5af9bb95919f35e66f614176543f6d1a/?vgnextoid=c1a94154d7b3d010VgnVCM10000048f3d6a1RCRD&amp;vgnextchannel=db029c7755cb9010VgnVCM10000045f3d6a1RCRD"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">Form
    AR-11</span></a></span><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:
    italic">), to OIS by email </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="mailto:ois@uic.edu"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;
    mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">ois@uic.edu</span></a></span><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:italic">, and via
    UIC&rsquo;s </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="https://www.hr.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=4292&amp;pageId=858105"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">My
    Profile</span></a></span><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic"> page.&nbsp;If your H is pending at USCIS,
    print AR-11 or call 1-800-375-5283.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><strong><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Immigration_Site_Visits">Immigration Site Visits</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">USCIS&rsquo; FDNS (Fraud Detection and National
    Security) unit must conduct random site visits on 20,000 H-1B workers
    every year.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">FDNS usually contacts OIS first. If an FDNS
    officer appears at your work place, please ask to see identification and
    contact OIS immediately.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">FDNS inspectors are verifying your work
    information and may take photographs of your lab/office space as well as
    ask you questions related to your employment.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Legal_Permanent_Residence_(LPR)/Green_Card">Legal Permanent Residence (LPR)/Green Card</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">H-1B status is &ldquo;dual intent,&rdquo; unlike other
    non-immigrant statuses; you may file for LPR while in H-1B status: see our
    </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="https://www.ois.uic.edu/departments/use_of_attorneys_policy/"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">Use of
    Attorneys Policy</span></a></span><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic"> and <a href="https://www.ois.uic.edu/departments/permanent_residency"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">UIC
    Sponsorship of Permanent Immigrant Visas and Consular Processing</span></a>
    web pages.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">If you obtain LPR/a green card, please send a
    copy to OIS as soon as possible to close your OIS record.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">
<h2 id="Taxes">Taxes</h2>
</strong><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"></span>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-line-height-alt:1.15pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3">Individuals in H
    status are required to file both state and federal taxes.</li>
</ul>
<strong>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">
</strong></strong><strong>
<h2 id="Travel_and_Visa_Process">Travel and Visa Process</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
    <li><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">Schedule an appointment with the </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="http://www.usembassy.gov/"><span>U.S. Consulate/Embassy</span></a></span><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"> and complete Form DS-160 with fee.&nbsp; </span></li>
    <li><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">Review consulate/embassy website for guidance about required documents.&nbsp;We suggest bringing:</span>
    <ul type="circle">
        <li class="" style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"><span>Passport (valid for six months beyond reentry date)</span></li>
        <li class="" style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"><span>Original H-1B Approval Notice</span></li>
        <li class="" style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"><span>Copy of Labor Condition Application (ETA Form 9035) and I-129 petition</span></li>
        <li class="" style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"><span>Employment offer or recently dated sponsoring department letter</span></li>
        <li class="" style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"><span>Copies of most recent earnings statements</span></li>
        <li class="" style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"><span>If a former J-1 Exchange Visitor:&nbsp; copies of all prior Forms DS-2019, original I-612 Approval Notice or Advisory Opinion letter</span></li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">H-4s</span></strong><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">:&nbsp; In addition to the above, they should bring proof of marriage, or birth, when applying for a visa.&nbsp;If they are traveling independently from you, they should carry your original I-797 approval notice, or their own original H-4 I-797 approval notice, if they have one.&nbsp; </span></li>
    <li><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">Automatic Visa Revalidation exception</span></strong><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">: H-1Bs (and H-4s) may travel to Canada and Mexico with an expired visa for less than 30 days. Other exceptions may apply, please see our </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="https://www.ois.uic.edu/faculty__staff__and_scholars/travel___visas"><span>website</span></a></span><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);"> for additional travel details.</span></li>
</ul>
<strong><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">
<h2> </h2>
</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
</ul>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Travel_and_Visa_Process"></h2>
</strong></strong></div>
<strong>
<h2 id="Grace_Periods">Grace Periods</h2>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">You have a 10-day grace period after the end
    date of your I-797 approval notice.&nbsp;You may not work during this
    period; it is time to prepare to leave the U.S., change status, etc.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">If your department ends your employment before
    the I-797 end date, as above, you have 60 days to remain in the country
    and have a new sponsor file a petition for you.&nbsp; (See &ldquo;portability&rdquo;
    below.)</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Portability">Portability</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">It is possible to &ldquo;port&rdquo; or &ldquo;transfer&rdquo; your
    H-1B status to another employer/institution; the new employer will file a
    Form I-129 on your behalf. </span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Employment should be continuous from UIC to
    the next employer. If your department ends your employment early, you may
    have up to 60 days to remain in the country and seek other employment. You
    may not work or volunteer during the transitional time. Your future H-1B
    sponsor will notify you when you may begin your new employment.&nbsp; </span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">Please consult with your new employer for
    details on this process.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Departure">Departure</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">You must submit a </span><span style="color: rgb(31, 73, 125);"><a href="https://www.ois.uic.edu/faculty__staff__and_scholars/forms"><span style="mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri">Departure
    Verification Form</span></a></span><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic"> upon completion of employment. This form is
    required regardless of your departure reason:&nbsp; leaving the U.S.,
    changing employers, or changing immigration status.</span></li>
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">If your department ends your employment before
    the I-797 end date, you must be offered a return ticket to your home
    country, which you may accept or decline.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;mso-line-height-alt:
1.15pt"><span style="color: rgb(127, 127, 127);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="Unlawful_Presence">Unlawful Presence</h2>
</strong>
<ul style="margin-top:0in" type="disc">
    <li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#7F7F7F;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;
    mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;
    mso-bidi-font-style:italic">This occurs when you stay beyond the ending
    date of your I-94 or upon determination by Department of Homeland
    Security. Consequences include a 3-year bar from reentering the U.S. if
    you have stayed unlawfully in the U.S. for 180 days or more, and a 10-year
    bar if you remain unlawfully in the U.S. for 360 days or more. Violation
    of your H-1B status makes you ineligible for any immigration benefits.
    This does not apply if a timely, non-frivolous petition to extend your
    stay has been received by the USCIS prior to the end date of your I-94. </span></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
</ul>
</strong></div>
